summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsCruelty FreeVeganSustainable PackagingDrunk Elephant's Protini Polypeptide Firming Moisturizer combines signal peptides, growth factors, supportive amino acids, and pygmy waterlily for immediate improvement in the appearance of skin's tone, texture, and firmness.
details: DetailsBenefitsReplenishes and restores skin to a visibly strong, healthy stateReduces the appearance of lines, wrinkles, and sun damageLeaves skin feeling strengthened and moisturizedRestores younger, revived-looking skinDermatologist TestedFormulated without the Suspicious 6 - Essential Oils, Silicones, Chemical Sunscreens, SLS, Fragrances + Dyes, and Drying AlcoholsFormulated at a skin-friendly pH of 4.0Key IngredientsSignal Peptide Complex (Growth Factors): nine signal peptides (made up of amino acids, which form proteins in the skin) bind moisture to skin - plumping, firming, and restoring bouncePygmy Waterlily Stem Cell Extract: an excellent source of antioxidants and nutrients to replenish the skin; this ingredient is extremely moisturizing, soothing, calming, and effective in supporting healthy, youthful-looking skinSoybean Folic Acid Ferment Extract: this B vitamin plays a central role in maintaining youthful, elastic skin; skin is thirsty for folic acid, especially after exposure to sunResearch ResultsIn a clinical study with 31 people after 8 weeks:96% showed improvement in skin's tone, radiance, and luminosity93% showed improvement in texture90% showed improvement in skin's hydrationItem 2588434How To UseApply morning and night to clean, dry skin for the vital dose of protein and replenishing moisture the skin needs to retain its youthful appearance. Mix with any Drunk Elephant serum, cream, or oil as part of a total skincare solution.Tip: Think of Protini in your skincare routine like adding a shot of protein to your smoothie everyday.Smoothie Tip: "Absolute Power Smoothie" - 1 pump Protini Cream +1 pump B-Hydra +1 pump C-Firma, for brighter, firmer, more moisturized skin.IngredientsWater/Aqua/Eau, Dicaprylyl Carbonate, Glycerin, Cetearyl Alcohol, Cetearyl Olivate, Sorbitan Olivate, Sclerocarya Birrea Seed Oil, Bacillus/ Folic Acid Ferment Filtrate Extract, Nymphaea Alba Root Extract, sh-Oligopeptide-1, sh-Oligopeptide-2, sh-Polypeptide-1, sh-Polypeptide-9, sh-Polypeptide-11, Copper Palmitoyl Heptapeptide-14, Heptapeptide-15 Palmitate, Palmitoyl Tetrapeptide-7, Palmitoyl Tripeptide-1, Alanine, Arginine, Glycine, Histidine, Isoleucine, Phenylalanine, Proline, Serine, Threonine, Valine, Acetyl Glutamine, Coconut Alkanes, Coco-Caprylate/Caprate, Sodium Hyaluronate, Aspartic Acid, Linoleic Acid, Linolenic Acid, Lecithin, Butylene Glycol, Polyvinyl Alcohol, Sodium Lactate, Sodium PCA, PCA, Sorbitan Isostearate, Carbomer, Polysorbate 20, Polysorbate 60, Lactic Acid/Glycolic Acid Copolymer, Hydroxyethyl Acrylate/Sodium Acryloyldimethyl Taurate Copolymer, Xanthan Gum, Isomalt, 1,2-Hexanediol, Caprylyl Glycol, Chlorphenesin, Phenoxyethanol, Tocopherol, Sodium Benzoate, Phenylpropanol, Glyceryl Caprylate, Symphytum Officinale Callus Culture Extract.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: Amazing product
reviews.comments: Drunk elephant has the best products. This one is my favorite.

reviews.headline: Love how hydrating this moisturizer is.
reviews.comments: Love how hydrating this is!!

reviews.headline: Gentle and smooth
reviews.comments: I have very oily acne probe skin. I dont use any moisturizers on my face cuz i usually break out. Im 38 about to be 39. I saw the reviews and decided to buy it. It is expensive but i truly have to say its worth the price. I been using it for about 3/4 months now. I was using it consistantly the first month at night but i noticed maybe 1 day out of the week I was waking up with a tiny white head.   I use it a few times a week now. I actually like using it in the morning before i put my makeup on. My daughter whos 13 I caught using it and I laughed but she actually loves it haha .. i did notice the pump after a while wouldn't pump the cream out so i had to keep pumping and it started working fine adtwr that. A little goes a long way. My skin does feel a lil irritated if i clunk it on but if i put just the right anount its fine. Like i said, my skin is very sensitive. Its smooth, smells pleasant , lightweight and very moisturizing. I personally will continue to buy it. The peice is outrageous but you pay for what u get.

reviews.headline: Will continue to repurchase
reviews.comments: I bought this for the first time in 2023 (a smaller size). This moisturizer makes my skin feel hydrated without being greasy. It's very lightweight - this is a great moisturizer for folks with oily, combo, or normal skin. I have continued to repurchase this since and have gone through 4 of the 3.3oz size and 1 of the larger size they sell around the holidays. I have used similar moisturizers / dupes and haven't found anything that compares to it. Love the Protini Polypeptide Moisturizer! I'm not a fan of most other DE products, but this one is A++++.

reviews.headline: Don't waste your money
reviews.comments: I got this moisturizer and I heard amazing reviews about it. I got it while being indesicive on its price, but still got it to treat myself on my birthday. After about 1-2 uses I broke out so bad! Weird because I never ever break out. My skin is usually amazing and fine with products. This broke me out so bad to the point I was crying so hard to even move my face! I would never even think about buying again and would NOT recommend getting it. And my skin is a mixture of oily and dry. Although, I have tried other products from Drunk Elephant and they have been fine, so I guess this moisturizer just doesn't work for me. ü§∑‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

reviews.headline: Pleasantly surprised
reviews.comments: I needed an oil-free, cruelty-free moisturizer to replace my discontinued holy grail by another brand.  After trying a couple different brands that did not work out, I took a chance on this one.  I am pleasantly surprised by the results!  It is not greasy, and it verges on a matte finish without hitting that overdry consistency.  It does not cause my skin to go into overproduction of oil like others.  It goes on nice and smooth and absorbs evenly.  Some people may dislike the smell of this lotion--to me, it smells vaguely like wheat, and that is okay with me.  This product is a little on the expensive side, that is its only downfall.

reviews.headline: Got milks on my forehead while using this /:
reviews.comments: Drunk elephant has to be one of those hype brands because I've spent over $400 on their different products & have never seen positive results. I've bought this face cream a couple times & I get milia on my forehead & temple area everytime I use this. I wouldn't waste the money again after I stopped using it but if it works for you do you

reviews.headline: Great for sensitive skin
reviews.comments: Solid option‚Äîmoisturizes and rich but not heavy. Absorbs easily. Goes well under makeup. Does not irritate my skin‚Äîyay!

reviews.headline: NEVER REFORMULATE
reviews.comments: I have never in my life found a moisturizer that contains all of the incredible ingredients this one does. Seriously, just look it up on incidecoder. I have been using this moisturizer for years, regardless of price, and will use it for the actual rest of my life if this formula never changes. Some other DE products can be hit-or-miss, but this is a true holy grail for me.

reviews.headline: Love it
reviews.comments: I have very sensitive skin! Big pores acne for years. I'm 38 and never use face moisturizer because I feel like since my skin is an oil pit already it was gonna make it worse but I'm in love. Soft and gentle on my skin. 2 weeks already and will continue to use .

reviews.headline: Always my go to!!!'

reviews.headline: What Happened
reviews.comments: Why is every review of this product from a gift!?! I have been using this for a few years now and several months ago, there was a recall on the product. After the recall, I began purchasing again and the formula is not the same at all. It's heavy, doesn't absorb well and the texture is just different. It is definitely no longer worth the cost and I am looking for a replacement.

reviews.headline: Hydrating for sensitive skin!!
reviews.comments: Drunk Elephant's Protini Polypeptide Cream is a standout in the skincare world. Its lightweight yet deeply moisturizing formula is packed with peptides, amino acids, and growth factors that work to nourish and strengthen the skin. The cream absorbs quickly, leaving the skin feeling hydrated, plump, and smooth without any greasy residue. It's ideal for all skin types, including sensitive skin, and helps improve the skin's texture and elasticity over time. The clean, fragrance-free formula is a bonus for those with sensitive skin, making it a must-try for anyone looking to enhance their skincare routine. Gifted by drunk elephant

reviews.headline: Love this moisturizer
reviews.comments: This moisturizer was gifted by Drunk Elephant and I love it! I like to apply this moisturizer in the morning and under my makeup too. This moisturizer improved my skins texture and overall dryness.  Definitely my new favorite moisturizer!

reviews.headline: very hydrating!!
reviews.comments: This product was kindly gifted to me by Drunk Elephant and I have been using this for over a week and I can already see a difference in my skin! I usually have dry and dull skin and I have noticed how hydrated and plump my skin looks!

faceoff_positive.headline: Pocket perfect!

faceoff_negative.comments: It felt great the first three days and then I had an allergic reaction and it burned my face. My skin began to peel, I had red dry splotches all around my mouth and chin and temple areas and it took 5 days to heal. It looked like a chemical burn.     I'm giving my face a wk off and trying it again. I want to make sure the allergic reaction was not an isolated event and that it was truly as of a resold of the cream.     The second issue I have is that my bottle had an air bubble in the bottom of it when I opened it and it was half empty.
